HIGHWAY ADMINISTRATION TO COVER THE COSTS OF IMPLEMENTING AND
ADMINISTERING SAFETY CORRIDOR SPEED MONITORING SYSTEMS.
(II) AFTER THE DISTRIBUTION UNDER SUBPARAGRAPH (I) OF
THIS PARAGRAPH, THE REMAINING BALANCE SHALL BE DISTRIBUTED TO THE
TRANSPORTATION TRUST FUND FOR:
1. HIGHWAY SAFETY PURPOSES; AND
2. STATE HIGHWAY ADMINISTRATION SYSTEM
PRESERVATION.
(2) MONEY DISTRIBUTED TO THE STATE HIGHWAY ADMINISTRATION
UNDER PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS SUBSECTION IS SUPPLEMENTAL TO AND IS NOT
INTENDED TO TAKE THE PLACE OF FUNDING THAT WOULD OTHERWISE BE
APPROPRIATED FOR THE USES DESCRIBED UNDER PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS
SUBSECTION.
21–101.
